WEBVTT

1
00:00:04.560 --> 00:00:07.800
Ah... So that's Ryu-chan?

2
00:00:05.190 --> 00:00:08.900
Niiyama Girls'

3
00:00:07.800 --> 00:00:10.950
I know this is gonna sound rude, 
but what's so great about him?

4
00:00:11.410 --> 00:00:16.570
Ryu-chan and I were neighbors up until 
I moved away in fourth grade.

5
00:00:17.280 --> 00:00:19.080
Hey, giant girl.

6
00:00:19.080 --> 00:00:22.290
Make sure 
to do your 
proper 
greetings

7
00:00:19.370 --> 00:00:22.290
Don't just stop there. 
We humans can't get by!

8
00:00:24.710 --> 00:00:27.860
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

9
00:00:28.250 --> 00:00:31.210
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey!

10
00:00:32.600 --> 00:00:34.820
Crap! It's Tanaka from Class 2!

11
00:00:35.360 --> 00:00:38.790
Hey, you're really tall and 
super cool, so straighten up!

12
00:00:40.710 --> 00:00:43.740
Okay, I'm gonna take you to 
the best place ever today.

13
00:00:46.940 --> 00:00:48.610
Comin' through!

14
00:00:48.610 --> 00:00:51.940
Ryunosuke! I told you to 
quit with that greeting!

15
00:01:02.970 --> 00:01:04.840
I don't know how to explain it...

16
00:01:04.840 --> 00:01:07.980
But he really helped me build up 
confidence in myself...

17
00:01:07.980 --> 00:01:11.540
Uh-huh, really? Right...

18
00:01:12.760 --> 00:01:14.840
I didn't say anything to 
embarrass you that much!

19
00:01:14.840 --> 00:01:16.180
How shy are you?!

20
00:01:22.550 --> 00:01:25.350
I... have a chance?

21
00:01:25.920 --> 00:01:27.050
How about I walk you home?

22
00:01:27.050 --> 00:01:28.290
That's okay.

23
00:01:28.290 --> 00:01:29.260
I'll hold that for you!

24
00:01:29.260 --> 00:01:30.390
Just practice.

25
00:01:31.670 --> 00:01:35.160
I didn't stand a chance up until now...

26
00:01:35.590 --> 00:01:38.050
But now I have a chance...

27
00:01:38.050 --> 00:01:39.320
Which means I...

28
00:01:42.210 --> 00:01:44.680
I've just been born.

29
00:01:44.680 --> 00:01:46.650
Uh, Tanaka? Get a grip!

30
00:01:46.650 --> 00:01:48.520
You've been alive this whole time.

31
00:01:48.520 --> 00:01:49.950
This is all your fault, Ennoshita!

32
00:01:49.950 --> 00:01:51.220
Yeah, whatever.

33
00:02:08.600 --> 00:02:14.270
Haikyu!!

34
00:03:07.540 --> 00:03:08.710
Miyagi


Karasuno

35
00:03:22.300 --> 00:03:26.310
Episode 13: The Second Day

36
00:03:24.470 --> 00:03:26.430
Great job today.

37
00:03:27.080 --> 00:03:30.280
I'm sure that you're already 
thinking about tomorrow,

38
00:03:30.280 --> 00:03:33.400
but please, allow me to say this.

39
00:03:34.210 --> 00:03:37.820
Congratulations on your important 
victory at nationals.

40
00:03:37.820 --> 00:03:39.320
Yeah!

41
00:03:41.780 --> 00:03:44.740
All right, let's talk about tomorrow.

42
00:03:47.610 --> 00:03:52.210
I mean... The reality isn't gonna 
change, so I'll just say it...

43
00:03:52.460 --> 00:03:56.130
We're going up against the second-place 
team from this year's Inter-High.

44
00:03:56.210 --> 00:03:57.540
Inarizaki High School

45
00:03:58.340 --> 00:04:01.820
Inarizaki High School, representing Hyogo.

46
00:04:01.820 --> 00:04:03.900
Well, you know...

47
00:04:03.900 --> 00:04:06.220
You can call them the favorites 
to win this whole thing.

48
00:04:08.390 --> 00:04:11.770
First, their top scorer 
is their #4, Ojiro Aran.

49
00:04:12.310 --> 00:04:13.930
He's both very tall and powerful.

50
00:04:13.930 --> 00:04:15.820
Just like Fukurodani's Bokuto,

51
00:04:15.820 --> 00:04:18.690
he's just outside of being one 
of the top three hitters in Japan.

52
00:04:19.200 --> 00:04:23.650
And when he's on his game, 
he has the ability to surpass that.

53
00:04:24.160 --> 00:04:26.040
Just like when we faced Ushiwaka,

54
00:04:26.040 --> 00:04:30.250
you always need to think about 
stopping him and getting the ball.

55
00:04:30.250 --> 00:04:32.420
We'll counter him with our total defense.

56
00:04:34.120 --> 00:04:38.090
And this is their middle blocker, #10 Suna Rintaro.

57
00:04:38.520 --> 00:04:41.550
He's actually shorter than 
most middle blockers

58
00:04:42.020 --> 00:04:44.650
but his instincts are on point.

59
00:04:44.650 --> 00:04:46.730
Make sure you're constantly 
on him when he attacks.

60
00:04:47.600 --> 00:04:50.490
He'll definitely get used 
to our quick attack, too.

61
00:04:50.490 --> 00:04:53.060
Make sure you take advantage of the 
space you have when you attack.

62
00:04:54.920 --> 00:04:57.910
Ojiro and Suna are 
Inarizaki's main guns,

63
00:04:57.910 --> 00:05:00.690
but the one that's going 
to cause real trouble

64
00:05:01.030 --> 00:05:05.400
is the one who can precisely all 
of the spikers, including those two...

65
00:05:05.400 --> 00:05:08.000
Their setter, Miya Atsumu.

66
00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:10.720
Kageyama, you probably met him
 at the youth training camp.

67
00:05:10.720 --> 00:05:11.370
Yes.

68
00:05:11.370 --> 00:05:15.370
That guy's said to be the 
best setter high school...

69
00:05:17.340 --> 00:05:21.150
Supposedly, the way he sets
 the ball makes it look

70
00:05:21.150 --> 00:05:22.710
like the spiker's gotten better.

71
00:05:22.710 --> 00:05:24.840
To be honest, his sets 
are really easy to hit.

72
00:05:24.840 --> 00:05:27.000
They're consistent and don't waver.

73
00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:29.370
You're actually admitting that?

74
00:05:29.860 --> 00:05:33.760
Well, his setting isn't the only 
thing we have to watch out for.

75
00:05:33.760 --> 00:05:34.720
His serves.

76
00:05:34.720 --> 00:05:35.560
Yeah.

77
00:05:36.790 --> 00:05:41.510
Miya-san's basically been dual-wielding spike
serves and jump floaters for a while now.

78
00:05:42.020 --> 00:05:45.900
So we won't know what he'll hit us
 with until the last second.

79
00:05:46.440 --> 00:05:49.540
It'll be hard to form a
 serve-receive formation, then.

80
00:05:49.540 --> 00:05:51.530
I heard that he earned the best server award

81
00:05:51.530 --> 00:05:53.870
at both the Inter-Middle 
and Inter-High tournaments.

82
00:05:54.800 --> 00:05:56.950
I really didn't need to hear that...

83
00:05:58.310 --> 00:05:59.040
Sorry.

84
00:06:02.210 --> 00:06:07.010
We just won a game, but everyone 
already looks terrifyingly serious.

85
00:06:07.590 --> 00:06:09.120
The second seed...

86
00:06:09.120 --> 00:06:11.370
Out of the dozens of teams listed here,

87
00:06:11.370 --> 00:06:14.890
we get stuck playing the second-best team?

88
00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:17.980
The top two teams in the country...

89
00:06:18.580 --> 00:06:21.230
That means we get to play both of them!

90
00:06:25.090 --> 00:06:29.400
That's if the top seed Itachiyama 
makes it all the way to the finals.

91
00:06:29.400 --> 00:06:31.370
They're in the other block.

92
00:06:31.370 --> 00:06:32.680
Oh, yeah.

93
00:06:32.680 --> 00:06:36.090
But then whatever team beat Itachiyama 
 would become the best, right?

94
00:06:36.090 --> 00:06:37.210
Oh, yeah...

95
00:06:38.150 --> 00:06:39.020
Wait, what?

96
00:06:39.020 --> 00:06:42.130
I just can't with you two... I really can't.

97
00:06:42.130 --> 00:06:44.620
How are you two so ridiculously confident?!

98
00:06:54.900 --> 00:06:56.270
Man, it's cold...

99
00:06:59.730 --> 00:07:16.700
Karasuno High School 
Volleyball Club

100
00:07:02.870 --> 00:07:05.840
Hey, Asahi. You can do that thing now.

101
00:07:05.840 --> 00:07:06.600
Huh?

102
00:07:07.280 --> 00:07:10.850
The thing where you mention that it's 
finally our last tournament, or something.

103
00:07:10.850 --> 00:07:12.860
I didn't let you say it at the Inter-High.

104
00:07:13.380 --> 00:07:15.820
This probably isn't the time for that.

105
00:07:17.050 --> 00:07:18.070
It's sorta weird, though.

106
00:07:18.480 --> 00:07:22.710
When you're all panicky, I somehow 
don't feel panicky for once.

107
00:07:24.280 --> 00:07:25.770
Oh, shut up.

108
00:07:43.810 --> 00:07:46.030
Looks like both the energetic 
crew and the airheaded crew

109
00:07:46.030 --> 00:07:48.110
finally ran down their batteries.

110
00:07:48.110 --> 00:07:51.350
Well, everything's been a bit different, 
including our warm ups.

111
00:07:51.890 --> 00:07:55.700
They were probably way more 
tired than they realized.

112
00:07:56.240 --> 00:07:59.950
Jaybird Inn

113
00:07:56.720 --> 00:07:58.590
We all need to make sure we don't get hurt.

114
00:07:58.590 --> 00:07:59.950
Yeah.

115
00:07:59.950 --> 00:08:03.710
Mentally
Tough

116
00:08:04.240 --> 00:08:08.280
Damn it, what the hell? Am I nervous?

117
00:08:08.280 --> 00:08:13.660
No, this is one of those situations where 
my adrenaline's just pumpin'...

118
00:08:13.660 --> 00:08:15.320
Oh, Ryu-chan.

119
00:08:15.320 --> 00:08:16.440
Oh...

120
00:08:16.440 --> 00:08:18.890
Oh, hey, Kanoka...

121
00:08:19.440 --> 00:08:21.320
You've definitely got a chance.

122
00:08:24.020 --> 00:08:26.680
I guess it's pretty cold in Tokyo, too.

123
00:08:27.410 --> 00:08:28.860
Yeah...

124
00:08:28.860 --> 00:08:30.650
How's Saeko-chan doing?

125
00:08:31.860 --> 00:08:34.640
She's good... How's your family?

126
00:08:34.640 --> 00:08:36.810
They're all doing well.

127
00:08:47.550 --> 00:08:48.520
Ryu-chan...

128
00:08:49.880 --> 00:08:52.460
So, um... I...

129
00:08:52.460 --> 00:08:57.140
You've got a chance
 It's not even just a chance
 You've definitely got a chance
Chance   Chance   Chance   Chance   Chance   Chance   Chance   Chance

130
00:08:52.800 --> 00:08:56.520
I... I... I... I...

131
00:08:57.140 --> 00:09:03.160
S-Sorry! I already have 
my heart set on another!

132
00:09:00.990 --> 00:09:03.740
What are you doing, Kanoka? Wait inside.

133
00:09:03.740 --> 00:09:04.900
It's cold out here.

134
00:09:15.330 --> 00:09:17.420
Kanoka grew into a beautiful young woman.

135
00:09:17.420 --> 00:09:18.950
The city at night...

136
00:09:18.950 --> 00:09:20.740
An older city boy...

137
00:09:22.310 --> 00:09:25.210
Did I... just completely...

138
00:09:26.340 --> 00:09:28.280
misunderstand the situation?

139
00:09:29.170 --> 00:09:32.490
Pretend I never said anything!

140
00:09:30.530 --> 00:09:31.380
Huh?!

141
00:09:33.890 --> 00:09:37.590
Oh, hey. My mom hand-stitched 
this again, but...

142
00:09:38.050 --> 00:09:40.390
Certain Victory
You can do it, Kanoka

143
00:09:44.320 --> 00:09:49.350
Ko-niichan... I think I might've 
just gotten my heart broken.

144
00:09:49.350 --> 00:09:52.540
Huh?! U-Uh, it'll be okay?

145
00:09:52.540 --> 00:09:54.870
Sorry, it's nothing...

146
00:09:55.960 --> 00:09:58.620
I didn't come here to fall in love.

147
00:09:58.620 --> 00:10:00.320
O-Oh, really?

148
00:10:02.260 --> 00:10:05.290
I'm... going to win every game.

149
00:10:12.320 --> 00:10:14.190
We're the second game.

150
00:10:14.190 --> 00:10:17.130
We can practice on the court 
at 8 AM for thirty minutes.

151
00:10:17.130 --> 00:10:18.120
Let's be quick.

152
00:10:18.120 --> 00:10:19.540
Right!

153
00:10:21.480 --> 00:10:24.430
Pardon me. Spiking drills 
are up next, right?

154
00:10:24.430 --> 00:10:25.140
Huh?

155
00:10:25.140 --> 00:10:26.600
Um...

156
00:10:27.730 --> 00:10:30.540
Is he the coach for Inarizaki?

157
00:10:30.540 --> 00:10:32.600
He definitely seems used to all of this!

158
00:10:34.780 --> 00:10:37.160
We'd like to spend some more 
time serving if that's all right!

159
00:10:41.090 --> 00:10:44.160
If their setter, Miya Atsumu,
 is super awesome,

160
00:10:44.490 --> 00:10:47.360
then we should probably aim for him 
when we send the ball back, right?

161
00:10:47.360 --> 00:10:49.720
Yeah! That's a super smart idea, Shoyo!

162
00:10:49.720 --> 00:10:50.870
Hang on, now...

163
00:10:51.440 --> 00:10:55.600
The recording we saw just now was 
of their qualifier finals match,

164
00:10:55.600 --> 00:10:57.740
but during that game, the 
player who they usually have

165
00:10:57.740 --> 00:11:00.580
in the opposite position wasn't at 
a hundred percent, so he sat out.

166
00:11:01.330 --> 00:11:04.970
The opposite... The player who stands 
opposite of the setter, right?

167
00:11:04.970 --> 00:11:08.410
The same position as Sawamura-san 
and Ushiwaka-san.

168
00:11:09.940 --> 00:11:14.590
There's a good chance that they're 
going to have that player this time.

169
00:11:19.990 --> 00:11:21.740
That's right...

170
00:11:21.740 --> 00:11:24.070
"Even if you manage to contain Miya Atsumu,"

171
00:11:24.070 --> 00:11:26.660
"his twin brother Osamu will make up for him."

172
00:11:27.590 --> 00:11:30.620
The best twins in the high 
school volleyball scene...

173
00:11:31.320 --> 00:11:32.890
The Miya Brothers.

174
00:11:35.000 --> 00:11:42.010
Haikyu!!

175
00:11:42.010 --> 00:11:49.020
Haikyu!!

176
00:11:51.270 --> 00:11:54.830
Inarizaki's first match is today, 
so how's the team doing?

177
00:11:54.830 --> 00:11:55.590
Right.

178
00:11:56.180 --> 00:12:00.240
The first match can be rather scary 
and nerve-racking for any team,

179
00:12:00.240 --> 00:12:02.480
but we're all pretty calm.

180
00:12:00.570 --> 00:12:05.450
Inarizaki High School Captain 
Kita Shinsuke

181
00:12:02.480 --> 00:12:06.160
We're in top shape, so I'm
 pretty confident we'll be fine.

182
00:12:06.160 --> 00:12:09.070
So what's your goal for this tournament?

183
00:12:07.010 --> 00:12:09.070
Hey, isn't that Machino,
 the announcer lady?

184
00:12:09.070 --> 00:12:10.660
To win, of course.

185
00:12:10.660 --> 00:12:11.690
Who's that?!

186
00:12:11.690 --> 00:12:15.230
What if she tries to interview 
us, too? What should we do?

187
00:12:15.230 --> 00:12:17.470
They're only talking to powerhouse 
schools, aren't they?

188
00:12:17.470 --> 00:12:19.970
Don't worry. They won't come to us.

189
00:12:19.970 --> 00:12:21.380
Right...

190
00:12:21.380 --> 00:12:24.320
Yamaguchi! Peace signs! Let's 
go throw up some peace signs!

191
00:12:23.960 --> 00:12:24.680
Huh?

192
00:12:24.320 --> 00:12:25.390
Please don't.

193
00:12:25.390 --> 00:12:27.140
I ended up getting told off, too!

194
00:12:28.210 --> 00:12:29.240
Listen up.

195
00:12:29.240 --> 00:12:33.470
You're way more impressive 
than you seem to realize!

196
00:12:33.470 --> 00:12:35.400
That goes for your face and your body!

197
00:12:35.400 --> 00:12:38.190
It's not like Ryu-chan 
has a girlfriend, right?

198
00:12:38.190 --> 00:12:39.520
Then keep pushing!

199
00:12:40.240 --> 00:12:41.780
Keep pushing, and he'll be yours.

200
00:12:41.780 --> 00:12:43.110
But...

201
00:12:44.710 --> 00:12:46.450
Hey, Kanoka. What's wrong?

202
00:12:47.830 --> 00:12:50.620
I can't get any serves over at all...

203
00:12:51.440 --> 00:12:53.460
How can I get better?

204
00:12:57.190 --> 00:12:59.040
Just keep trying until you can!

205
00:13:02.290 --> 00:13:03.140
Okay!

206
00:13:05.920 --> 00:13:07.010
Yeah!

207
00:13:07.860 --> 00:13:11.370
She probably didn't take that 
in the direction I meant,

208
00:13:11.370 --> 00:13:12.520
but whatever.

209
00:13:12.680 --> 00:13:15.890
Karasuno High School 
Volleyball Club

210
00:13:17.160 --> 00:13:19.920
I'm so sorry for saying such weird 
things out of the blue yesterday!

211
00:13:19.920 --> 00:13:21.020
Forget I ever said anything!

212
00:13:21.020 --> 00:13:22.560
No, no, it's fine!

213
00:13:22.560 --> 00:13:24.350
I'm sorry that Nii-chan 
showed up out of nowhere.

214
00:13:24.350 --> 00:13:27.110
Wait. Did you always 
have an older brother?

215
00:13:27.110 --> 00:13:29.820
He's a cousin that lives over here.

216
00:13:29.820 --> 00:13:31.610
Whenever I have a match in the city,

217
00:13:31.610 --> 00:13:35.260
he always brings over 
good luck charms and other gifts.

218
00:13:35.260 --> 00:13:37.870
Hey, he sounds like a great guy.

219
00:13:38.550 --> 00:13:40.480
Huh? Then wait...

220
00:13:40.480 --> 00:13:44.060
Thinking it was a misunderstanding
 was a misunderstanding...

221
00:13:44.060 --> 00:13:45.590
So, um, I...

222
00:13:46.010 --> 00:13:49.400
I don't slouch anymore 
because of you, Ryu-chan.

223
00:13:46.010 --> 00:13:49.970
Niiyama Girls'

224
00:13:51.280 --> 00:13:54.600
I've gotten really good,
 so watch me, okay?

225
00:14:00.650 --> 00:14:07.400
A New Rising Star! 
 Amanai Kanoka
Niiyama Girls' High School
 (Miyagi)   Wing Spiker

226
00:14:00.820 --> 00:14:04.230
That's right... Kanoka is a lot better now.

227
00:14:04.720 --> 00:14:07.400
I'm the one who's getting left behind...

228
00:14:09.920 --> 00:14:11.130
I ain't gonna lose!

229
00:14:26.770 --> 00:14:28.170
Hinata, you dumbass!

230
00:14:28.630 --> 00:14:30.520
I wanna hurry up and start jumping!

231
00:14:30.520 --> 00:14:32.600
You look like you're rarin' to go.

232
00:14:34.230 --> 00:14:35.200
Heya.

233
00:14:35.200 --> 00:14:37.390
How're you doin', Tobio-kun?

234
00:14:37.390 --> 00:14:38.540
Fine, thanks.

235
00:14:38.540 --> 00:14:41.370
That one's Miya... Atsumu, right?

236
00:14:41.370 --> 00:14:43.060
Do your best out there today.

237
00:14:43.540 --> 00:14:47.780
I absolutely hate playin' 
against people who suck.

238
00:14:50.800 --> 00:14:51.800
Damn...

239
00:14:51.800 --> 00:14:53.160
Elites sure are scary.

240
00:14:53.420 --> 00:14:55.000
Yeah, sorry about that.

241
00:14:55.000 --> 00:14:57.370
Why are you apologizing?! 
Kageyama, you jerk!

242
00:14:57.710 --> 00:14:59.320
But I don't suck.

243
00:14:59.320 --> 00:15:01.080
Yes, I'm very aware of that.

244
00:15:01.080 --> 00:15:02.640
Though he sucks.

245
00:15:02.640 --> 00:15:04.090
How can you say that?!

246
00:15:04.870 --> 00:15:08.550
But he's not weak, so I think we'll be okay.

247
00:15:14.350 --> 00:15:16.930
The first match is in the 
middle of their second set.

248
00:15:21.600 --> 00:15:25.790
Even in our alternate uniforms, 
Noya-san looks like the star of the show!

249
00:15:25.790 --> 00:15:26.570
I know, right?

250
00:15:27.400 --> 00:15:29.820
Kageyama, orange really isn't your color.

251
00:15:29.820 --> 00:15:31.780
Shut up, you human tangerine.

252
00:15:31.780 --> 00:15:33.230
The hell did you say?!

253
00:15:33.230 --> 00:15:35.280
These do feel different, but what can we do?

254
00:15:35.280 --> 00:15:38.450
Inarizaki High School

255
00:15:35.970 --> 00:15:37.850
Our opponents are in black, too.

256
00:15:38.450 --> 00:15:41.520
You're somehow even more annoying now.

257
00:15:41.520 --> 00:15:42.800
Tsukishima!

258
00:15:42.800 --> 00:15:45.420
You're the last one who should 
probably be saying that, Tsukishima.

259
00:15:45.970 --> 00:15:50.300
Must be nice... How are they 
able to stay that calm?

260
00:15:50.300 --> 00:15:53.720
But you know, Hinata doesn't 
really get nervous anymore.

261
00:15:53.720 --> 00:15:54.270
Huh?

262
00:15:54.270 --> 00:15:57.310
He seems to be way more 
excited than nervous now.

263
00:15:57.310 --> 00:15:59.180
He's actually maturing.

264
00:16:00.020 --> 00:16:01.180
Oh, yeah. Earlier...

265
00:16:01.180 --> 00:16:06.360
Atsumu

266
00:16:01.180 --> 00:16:06.360
Osamu

267
00:16:01.560 --> 00:16:04.080
I saw some girls hold Miya Atsumu hand fans.

268
00:16:04.080 --> 00:16:05.800
What is he, an idol?

269
00:16:06.760 --> 00:16:09.310
He pretty much is.

270
00:16:09.310 --> 00:16:12.160
He's got a different kind of popularity 
than the champions, Itachiyama.

271
00:16:12.160 --> 00:16:14.820
He's definitely got the skills 
and impressive plays.

272
00:16:15.220 --> 00:16:18.600
He's the ultimate challenger that 
has both of those qualities.

273
00:16:18.600 --> 00:16:21.790
They feature him a lot on TV, too.

274
00:16:22.530 --> 00:16:26.540
No one in this arena even 
knows that we exist...

275
00:16:27.560 --> 00:16:30.470
What the heck, Daichi?! Get a grip!

276
00:16:32.900 --> 00:16:34.100
It gets me even more fired up!

277
00:16:36.420 --> 00:16:38.430
Looks like Daichi's finally back.

278
00:16:39.040 --> 00:16:41.720
You were pretty tame yesterday.

279
00:16:41.720 --> 00:16:43.600
I was just concentrating.

280
00:16:43.600 --> 00:16:45.600
All right, let's move.

281
00:16:48.720 --> 00:16:49.520
Right!

282
00:17:13.050 --> 00:17:16.010
Go, go, let's go! Let's go, Ina High!

283
00:17:15.730 --> 00:17:20.400
I really can't take their 
cheering section...

284
00:17:16.010 --> 00:17:19.080
Go, go, let's go! Let's go, Ina High!

285
00:17:20.400 --> 00:17:24.350
Does Inarizaki have a high-level 
marching band, too?

286
00:17:24.950 --> 00:17:26.270
My stomach...

287
00:17:26.270 --> 00:17:28.700
Those huge horns are super cool!

288
00:17:29.310 --> 00:17:30.970
Atsumu!

289
00:17:29.310 --> 00:17:32.280
Miya Osamu                         Miya Atsumu

290
00:17:30.970 --> 00:17:32.280
Aran!

291
00:17:32.280 --> 00:17:34.040
Osamu!

292
00:17:34.040 --> 00:17:36.280
Miya-senpai!

293
00:17:38.180 --> 00:17:39.670
All right, let's go!

294
00:17:40.530 --> 00:17:41.370
Let's go!

295
00:17:41.960 --> 00:17:42.760
Let's go!

296
00:17:43.240 --> 00:17:45.210
LET'S GO!

297
00:17:45.210 --> 00:17:47.670
Yeah!

298
00:17:45.330 --> 00:17:48.960
Official Warm Ups

299
00:17:50.130 --> 00:17:51.090
Yeah!

300
00:17:51.800 --> 00:17:53.760
Inarizaki                                                Karasuno

301
00:17:53.040 --> 00:17:53.760
Nice kill!

302
00:17:54.170 --> 00:17:55.720
Last one!

303
00:17:58.280 --> 00:18:00.050
Soul swap delayed spike!

304
00:18:02.100 --> 00:18:03.220
Wow!

305
00:18:03.220 --> 00:18:04.970
Uh, I'm pretty sure that's 
not a delayed spike.

306
00:18:04.970 --> 00:18:06.090
I think he just wanted to say that.

307
00:18:06.090 --> 00:18:07.710
Did the setter just spike right now?

308
00:18:07.710 --> 00:18:09.080
That was actually pretty good.

309
00:18:09.080 --> 00:18:11.760
But isn't the guy who set even better?

310
00:18:11.760 --> 00:18:13.320
Good job, Miyas!

311
00:18:20.700 --> 00:18:22.490
Hinata, nice kill!

312
00:18:22.490 --> 00:18:24.660
Man, that kid sure can jump.

313
00:18:27.120 --> 00:18:28.830
Inarizaki                                                           Karasuno

314
00:18:30.580 --> 00:18:32.130
Miya Osamu                         Miya Atsumu

315
00:18:33.090 --> 00:18:37.130
All right, the match between the Hyogo 
representative, Inarizaki High School,

316
00:18:34.130 --> 00:18:37.130
Inarizaki High School

317
00:18:37.130 --> 00:18:41.340
Miyagi


Karasuno

318
00:18:37.450 --> 00:18:42.140
and the Miyagi Prefecture representative, 
Karasuno High School, is about to begin!

319
00:18:43.250 --> 00:18:44.810
Let's play!

320
00:18:46.000 --> 00:18:47.270
All right!

321
00:18:47.580 --> 00:18:52.730
Damn it... Why are we 
freaking out? Calm down!

322
00:18:54.500 --> 00:18:58.680
No one thought Karasuno 
would beat Shiratorizawa.

323
00:18:59.920 --> 00:19:02.660
Let's surprise everyone yet again!

324
00:19:03.100 --> 00:19:04.870
Yeah!

325
00:19:21.050 --> 00:19:24.010
We Don't Need the Memories

326
00:19:26.430 --> 00:19:28.520
Wh-What the heck was that?! 
That was super cool!

327
00:19:29.980 --> 00:19:33.710
Ready...

328
00:19:31.640 --> 00:19:32.350
Uh-oh.

329
00:19:33.710 --> 00:19:34.310
...go!

330
00:19:38.070 --> 00:19:40.030
We Don't Need the Memories

331
00:19:40.030 --> 00:19:41.490
Osamu

332
00:19:40.030 --> 00:19:41.490
Atsumu

333
00:19:40.030 --> 00:19:41.490
Nice serve!

334
00:19:41.960 --> 00:19:45.020
Hey, loosen up a bit. 
You guys are stiff as boards!

335
00:19:45.020 --> 00:19:47.360
It's not like he's throwing knives at you!

336
00:19:47.360 --> 00:19:47.950
Right!

337
00:19:48.950 --> 00:19:50.160
He's looking at us!

338
00:19:50.980 --> 00:19:54.030
Don't interrupt my serve again,

339
00:19:54.030 --> 00:19:55.840
you squealin' pigs.

340
00:19:56.660 --> 00:20:00.360
Sorry. Could you keep it 
down during the serves?

341
00:19:57.130 --> 00:20:04.340
Osamu

342
00:19:57.130 --> 00:20:04.340
Atsumu

343
00:20:00.360 --> 00:20:01.840
Wh-What?

344
00:20:01.840 --> 00:20:04.340
They do it all the time on TV!

345
00:20:08.890 --> 00:20:09.440
O...

346
00:20:09.440 --> 00:20:10.250
...ut!

347
00:20:14.350 --> 00:20:16.060
Damn it!

348
00:20:16.060 --> 00:20:17.280
Lame.

349
00:20:17.280 --> 00:20:18.700
Shut yer trap!

350
00:20:19.120 --> 00:20:21.780
My serve toss got a bit away from me.

351
00:20:21.780 --> 00:20:23.740
Inarizaki                                                      Karasuno

352
00:20:26.770 --> 00:20:29.450
Asahi! Stay focused!

353
00:20:29.450 --> 00:20:31.410
We Don't Need the Memories

354
00:20:29.450 --> 00:20:31.410
Boo!

355
00:20:31.790 --> 00:20:34.880
Is the crowd... actually booing?

356
00:20:34.880 --> 00:20:36.620
At the server?

357
00:20:37.650 --> 00:20:41.040
They make sure to stay perfectly 
quiet for their own team's server,

358
00:20:41.040 --> 00:20:43.500
but make sure to be loud and cause 
a fuss when the opponents serve.

359
00:20:43.500 --> 00:20:45.690
Their fans are definitely trained.

360
00:20:51.120 --> 00:20:52.940
Uh-oh! It got caught on the net!

361
00:20:52.940 --> 00:20:53.690
Sorry.

362
00:20:53.690 --> 00:20:55.020
We'll get the next one!

363
00:20:55.600 --> 00:20:59.520
Both teams are showing strong serves as 
each side tries to build momentum.

364
00:21:01.380 --> 00:21:03.440
Could the one to keep our eye on this match

365
00:21:03.870 --> 00:21:06.430
be the one people are calling the 
top high school setter,

366
00:21:06.430 --> 00:21:09.120
Inarizaki's Miya Atsumu?

367
00:21:09.120 --> 00:21:14.370
Indeed. But we should keep our 
eyes on Karasuno's setter, as well.

368
00:21:14.650 --> 00:21:17.370
Karasuno High School's Kageyama Tobio...

369
00:21:17.370 --> 00:21:21.130
He's another skilled player who was invited 
to the All-Japan Youth Camp this year.

370
00:21:22.940 --> 00:21:25.590
We're definitely seeing a setter battle 
between the East and the West!

371
00:21:30.840 --> 00:21:31.930
That jump was really good!

372
00:21:39.190 --> 00:21:41.290
I forgot to hit!

373
00:21:41.290 --> 00:21:44.280
If you can't jump and hit at the 
same time, don't even try, dumbass!

374
00:21:45.220 --> 00:21:47.920
Did he just say that he forgot to hit?

375
00:21:47.920 --> 00:21:49.120
He did.

376
00:21:49.680 --> 00:21:54.370
Are you sayin' the jumps we've seen 
so far ain't the highest he can go?

377
00:21:55.200 --> 00:21:59.250
Is he really experimenting 
while playing against us?

378
00:22:03.630 --> 00:22:08.260
I figured Tobio-kun was the kind of guy who 
marched to the beat of his own drum...

379
00:22:16.100 --> 00:22:18.780
But apparently that kid's just as bad.

380
00:23:54.870 --> 00:24:00.540
Haikyu!!
